---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import TreeWorld from '../components/TreeWorld.astro';
---

<Base active="home">
  <!-- ───────────────────────── hero: a quick intro ───────────────────────── -->
  <section class="hero section">
    <div class="wrap hero__copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">An experiment in building software with AI agents</p>
      <h1>Software you can watch grow.</h1>
      <p class="hero__disclaimer">
        An honest heads-up: this site was written by AI&nbsp;agents. storytree is a one-person project
        right now — I'm a solo dev and a dad to a 3-year-old, short on spare hours and no great writer,
        so I've leaned on the very tools I'm building to put it into words and min-max the time I've
        got. The ideas are mine; the prose is the machine's.
      </p>
      <p class="lede">
        Building with AI&nbsp;agents is fast — and a blur. The code writes itself; the hard part is
        <em>seeing</em> what it built, trusting it, and keeping humans and agents pointed the same way.
        storytree turns a project into a living map.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───────────────────────── the live map, front and centre ───────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section--tight">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="demo-lead">
        Here's a whole system in storytree's map view — a made-up team-chat backend. Bigger trees have
        more behind them; red is where a check is failing. <strong>Hover or tap a tree</strong> to
        inspect a story, or click to pin it and light up everything it depends on.
      </p>
      <TreeWorld />

      <div class="dive prose">
        <p>
          That's the shape of it — a project grows as a map you can read instead of a wall of diffs,
          and the work stays out in the open where it can be checked. There's a lot more underneath:
          how the proof gates work, why a <a href="/landscape/">map of <em>intent</em> beats a mirror
          of the code</a>, and what we're trying to prove by building this way.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__cta">
          <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/how-it-works/">See how it works →</a>
          <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/get-involved/">Why this exists · get involved</a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero__note muted">
          Small on purpose. Invite-only for now — but the door to ask is wide open.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero { padding-top: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.4rem); padding-bottom: clamp(0.8rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem); }
  .hero__copy { max-width: 50rem; }
  .hero__copy h1 { margin-top: 0.2rem; margin-bottom: 0.55rem; }
  .hero__disclaimer {
    max-width: 42rem; margin: 0 0 1.2rem; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-faint); border-left: 3px solid var(--line-strong); padding-left: 0.9rem;
  }
  .hero em { font-style: italic; color: var(--ink); }

  .demo-lead { max-width: 44rem; color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .demo-lead strong { color: var(--ink); }

  .dive { margin-top: 1.9rem; max-width: 44rem; }
  .dive em { font-style: italic; }
  .hero__cta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.7rem; margin-top: 1.2rem; }
  .hero__note { margin-top: 1.1rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
</style>
